  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expanding the Protection and Promotion of Mental Health and Psychosocial Support for the Communities Affected by the Refugee Emergency in Cox&apos;s Bazar Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will build upon findings, lessons learned, and best practices noted during 2018-2019 to expand actions to address psychosocial and mental health support (MHPSS) offered to refugee and host communities in Cox&#x2019;s Bazar, Bangladesh. Main gaps detected during the previous programming period related to ensuring comprehensive and inclusive mental health and psychosocial response for beneficiaries, including a strong need for increasing community-based participation, accessible resources, capacity to detect those in need of specialized mental healthcare, and expanding service provision to include host communities. This next phase project will address these gaps, aiming to scale up MHPSS programming to increase outreach capacity and improve service provision towards achieving amore holistic, comprehensive and inclusive mental health and psychosocial response.</narrative>
  </description>
